A '''Vederala''' is a practitioner of [[traditional medicine]] ([[Ayurveda]] or [[Unani]]) in [[Sri Lanka]], an ''ayurvedic physician''. The term is derived from the [[Sanskrit]] ''vaid'', meaning '[[physician]]'. Vederala's pills or ''guli'' are traditional medicines rolled into [[tablet|pill]] form, generally of globular or oblong shape.

